<p><b>What is the mother philosophy of Hatha Yoga?</b> Hatha yoga Meaning: 'The Yoga of Force'. Many teachers equate Ha to mean 'Sun' and Tha to mean moon, and reason that the physical yoga practice is intended to 'balance' the Sun and Moon energies within us.</p>
<p><b>What is the father of yoga?</b> Maharishi Patanjali, rightly called "The Father of Yoga" compiled and refined various aspects of Yoga systematically in his "Yoga Sutras" (aphorisms).</p>
